/XXLIGHTING SHABBAT CANDLES/PR

/ITCandles are traditionally lit in the home. Many communities also light candles together at
the beginning of the /MDKabbalat Shabbat/XX service. For additional readings, see pages 732,
735-737, 797. On Shabbat H/±anukah the H/±anukah candles (page 672) are lit prior to
the Shabbat candles./PR

/PR

To light candles in all the worlds--/PR

that is Shabbat./PR

To light Shabbat candles/PR

is a soul-leap pregnant with potential/PR

into a splendid sea, in it the mystery/PR

of the fire of sunset./PR

Lighting the candles transforms/PR

my room into a river of light,/PR

my heart sets in an emerald waterfall./PR

Zelda (translator unknown)/XX/PR

* */PR

As the great doors of night are opening/PR

we come into the clean quiet room of Shabbat./PR

Let us be thankful, as we light these candles/PR

like eyes of holiness, for this moment of peace./PR

/PR

Let us savor the fruit of the vine,/PR

the blood of the earth that quickens us./PR

/PR

Let us be thankful for grain, fruit of grasses/PR

that feed the cow, the gazelle and us./PR

/PR

Let us be grateful for the children and the work/PR

of the week that are our own fruitfulness./PR

/PR

Let us as we eat never forget that food comes/PR

from the earth we must cherish and heal/PR

through labor we must respect and reward./PR

Marge Piercy/XX/PR

