 נ ר נ . A quotation from Mosesòs prayer to heal Miriam, "God,
please heal her" (Numbers 12:13). God is sought as the source of spiritual
healing--soul healing. In union with the divine we find release from the
pain of the futile cycle of searching and disappointment. Shabbat is our
refuge of acceptance, our shelter from cravings and strivings./PR

/SC/XXS.P.W./XX/PR

/PR

/SCD/XXERASH/XX. Our yearning for salvation is the human form of the will to live,
which is cosmic and characteristic of all living beings. In our case the will
to live is the will to abundant and harmonious living...Human nature is
part of the larger world of nature, and our salvation can only be conceived
as a manifestation of a divine power both within and beyond us./PR

/SC/XXM.M.K. (ADAPTED)/XX/PR

