maUF.zimad libi. My God, my heartòs beloved. The popular version, while
grammatically difficult, offers a clear sense of surrender, a central motif
of religious love poetry. All I want, O my God, is to be near you and
to feel your presence. These are the /ITonly/XX things my heart desires./PR

